postcontent:
I have a Winchester Model 1894 for sale. It has been well taken care of, with absolutely no rust and it has a bright and shiny bore. The receiver and magazine tube have a couple extremely light scratches that I cannot even get to show up on camera and do not penetrate the bluing. The wooden stock is in good shape with only a couple small nicks, again does not penetrate the finish. title: For Sale/Trade:  HK Fabarm S.A.T. 8
postcontent: HK FABARMSAT-8 shotgun (S.A.T.-8 stands for Semi-Automatic Tactical, 8 shots)was specially designed for security / police / self-defense applications, as well as for practical sport shooting. These shotguns are manufactured in a wide spectrum of models, with different stocks and options, but all are based on same action with patented features such as Tri-bore barrel profile and Pulse Piston gas operated action. FABARM SAT-8 shotguns are gas-operated, semi-automatic weapons. Gas piston is of ring type, and is located around the front of the magazine tube, below the barrel. The patented Pulse Piston system consists of a polymer brake ring which is compressed between the gas piston and operating rod, which is connected to the bolt group. Upon discharge, this brake provides constant velocity of recoiling parts (regardless of the power of ammunition used) through the self-adjustable friction between the polymer ring and outer surface of the magazine tube - the heavier the load and the higher is pressure in the barrel, the stronger the ring will be compressed and the more friction will be added to the whole operating system. Barrel locking is achieved by single swinging locking piece, which is installed in the top of the bolt. The locking piece engages the notch in the barrel extension, and drops (rotates)down when bolt is unlocked. Return spring is located around the magazine tube. Feed is from underbarrel tubular magazine, which holds 7 rounds (total capacity is 8 rounds, assuming that one round ischambered). Receiver is made from aluminum alloy, and features integral Picatinny rail. Furniture (for end and buttstock) are made from polymer. Barrels are made using FABARM's proprietary TriBore bore profile, and can be equipped with interchangeable chokes or muzzle brake /compensator.

title: For Sale:  Customized Ruger 10/22 with BSA Sweet 22 Scope
location: Near Faribault - South of Metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota
postcontent:
For sale is a Ruger 10/22 with digital camo and scope.  

The rifle is exceptionally clean and the serial number starts with “823-“ which makes it produced in 2013 according to this site:  

http://www.ruger.com/service/productHistory/RI-10-22.html


The scope sits on a Picatinny rail that allows for tactical items to be quickly attached and removed as the shooter desires.  The scope is a 3 – 9 x 40 BSA Sweet 22 which retails for ~$149.95 new.  This type of scope uses trajectory compensation technology that was originally designed for military snipers; however these hot new scopes are catching on fast with target shooters, varmint hunters, and plinkers who want to spend more time hitting and less time missing when they go to the range.  The Sweet 22 is calibrated for .22LR ammunition and ¼ MOA, this means one click will move the bullet ¼” at 100 yards.  That info was basically taken from these two sites and then my own nickels worth tossed in too: 

http://www.bsaoptics.com/scope.aspx?productID=345

http://www.bsaoptics.com/family.aspx?familyID=13&filter=%
